        {
          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/http_specific_formatter.cc\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/http_specific_formatter.h\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/stream_info_formatter.cc\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/stream_info_formatter.h\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/http_specific_formatter.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"HttpBuiltInCommandParser::getKnownFormatters\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/http_specific_formatter.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"RequestHeaderFormatter\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/http_specific_formatter.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ResponseHeaderFormatter\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/stream_info_formatter.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/stream_info_formatter.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"CommonDurationFormatter\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/stream_info_formatter.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"StreamInfoAddressFormatterProvider\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/http_specific_formatter.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"HttpBuiltInCommandParser::parse\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/formatter/stream_info_formatter.h\",\n      \"symbol\": \"StreamInfoFormatterBase\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The access log command operators in Envoy are implemented across multiple C++ files in the formatter subsystem. The %REQ% (request header) and %RESP% (response header) operators are implemented in http_specific_formatter.cc (lines 334-355), where the HttpBuiltInCommandParser class registers them in the getKnownFormatters() lookup table (line 330-421). The %REQ% operator creates RequestHeaderFormatter instances that extract headers from request headers (lines 135-150), while %RESP% creates ResponseHeaderFormatter instances that extract from response headers (lines 118-133).\\n\\nThe %DURATION% and %UPSTREAM_HOST% operators are implemented in stream_info_formatter.cc. The %DURATION% operator is registered at line 1034-1041 in the getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders() function, which uses StreamInfoDurationFormatterProvider to calculate the duration via stream_info.currentDuration(). The %UPSTREAM_HOST% operator is registered at lines 1084-1100 and uses StreamInfoAddressFormatterProvider::withPort() to extract the upstream host address from stream_info.upstreamInfo()->upstreamHost()->address().\\n\\nThe formatter registration system uses a lookup table pattern: HttpBuiltInCommandParser::getKnownFormatters() (http_specific_formatter.cc:330-421) handles HTTP-specific formatters like %REQ% and %RESP%, while getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders() (stream_info_formatter.cc:821-1757) handles stream information formatters including %DURATION% and %UPSTREAM_HOST%. The registration uses REGISTER_BUILT_IN_COMMAND_PARSER macro at line 443 of http_specific_formatter.cc, and the StreamInfoFormatterBase template class (stream_info_formatter.h:305-345) uses getKnownStreamInfoFormatterProviders() to instantiate the appropriate formatter provider based on the command name.\"\n}\n",
